<HEAD>Prisoners Smuggling Drugs In Dentures And Bandages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prisoners who were released to
attend court hearings or receive treatment in hospitals have
returned with illegal drugs hidden in their dentures and bandages,
an official was quoted as saying today.
   To stop the drug smuggling guards will search all inmates when
they return, Prisons Director Zainal Abidin Noor told The Star
newspaper.
   He also said double fencing had been erected around the prison
in Penang, 180 miles northwest of Kuala Lumpur, to stop people
throwing drugs over the wall of the prison to the inmates.
   He did not say how many prisoners had been caught smuggling
drugs.
