<HEAD>Two Killed in Helicopter-Plane Collision</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DILLINGHAM, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Manakotak Airways Cessna-207
collided with a helicopter Tuesday night, killing the two pilots
aboard the crafts, authorities said.
   No other people were aboard when the crafts collided in the air
2 miles south of Dillingham-Alaska Airport in southwest Alaska,
said police dispatcher Cari Brown.
   The taxi service plane was thrown into trees south of the
airport, while the helicopter crashed to the ground and burst into
flames about a dozen yards from a home, officials said.
   No one on the ground was injured, said Ms. Brown.
   Firefighters extinguished the blaze before it damaged the house,
said firefighter Bob King.
   The National Transportation Safety Board will investigate the
crash, Ms. Brown said.
