<HEAD>200-Pound Fiberglass Hippo Head Stolen From Miniature Golf Course</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thieves beheaded a fiberglass
hippopotamus at a miniature golf course after an unsuccessful try
at taking a 600-pound golf course whale, police said.
   ``It's the time of year we normally see a lot of
end-of-the-school-year pranks,'' said Knox County Sheriff's
Detective Larry Gray.
   He said the thieves apparently gave up trying to lug the
fiberglass whale onto a vehicle after dragging it part way off the
course, still under construction, sometime Friday or Saturday. The
thieves then took the 200-pound hippo head, he said.
