<HEAD>Jackson Sets TV Campaign for California</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jesse Jackson plans to spend between $500,000
and $750,000 on television commercials starting next week in
delegate-rich California, while avoiding TV advertising in New
Jersey.
   Voters in California, New Jersey and two other states wind up
the long Democratic primary season on June 7.
   Gerald Austin, Jackson's campaign manager said Tuesday the
