<1ST_LINE>r p PM-PoliticalQuotes     05-25 0118</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Political Quotes,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, criticizing President Reagan's veto on Tuesday
of a massive trade bill because it contains a provision requiring
early notice of plant closings: ``Any administration that is
willing to give Gen. (Manuel Antonio) Noriega 120 days notice and a
plea bargain ought to be willing to give the American worker 60
days notice before they are thrown out on the street.''
   
   REP. LYNN MARTIN, R-Ill., a Bush supporter, commenting on polls
that show the vice president trailing Dukakis: ``We have bad polls.
If this were October, we'd be suicidal. But it's May.''
</TEXT>
