<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Bing-Arrest     05-25 0237</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Bing-Arrest,0244</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lady Bing Arrested For Keeping Husband Out Late</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of former Metropolitan Opera impresario
Sir Rudolf Bing has been arrested a second time after she kept her
husband out late in violation of a court order, police said.
   Carroll Douglass Bing, 48, was charged with violating the court
order of protection and third-degree assault, said Sgt. Raymond
O'Donnell, a police spokesman.
   She was supposed to have her 86-year-old husband, who suffers
from Alzheimer's disease, back to their apartment by 9 p.m., but
was about two hours late Tuesday, said O'Donnell, who did not know
where the couple had spent the evening.
   ``Then when she did return, she got involved in a dispute with a
40-year-old nurse,'' pushing her against a wall and bruising her
head, he said. The nurse declined medical treatment.
   Security guards at the apartment house called police, he said.
   Lady Bing was arrested May 12 after she allegedly violated the
court order issued three days before by state Judge Carmen
Ciparick. The judge ordered that she stay away from her husband for
six hours a day so nurses can care for him.
   The Manhattan district attorney's office declined to prosecute
her at that time.
   Lady Bing is in a civil court fight with her husband's lawyer,
Paul Goldhamer, who charges that she has abused Bing and has asked
the judge to annul the Bings' 1{-year-old marriage.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
