<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Britain-Rowntree     05-25 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Britain-Rowntree,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Candy Bar Deals Won't Be Referred To Merger Commission</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The British government today cleared the way for
Swiss food giant Nestle S.A.'s hostile bid for British confectioner
Rowntree PLC by saying the deal will not be referred to the
Monopolies and Mergers Commission.
   The Department of Trade and Industry also announced that the
acquisition by another Swiss company, Jacob Suchard S.A., of a
29.9-percent holding in Rowntree would not be referred to the
commission, either.
   Rowntree's share price soared on the morning announcement. After
moving down 9.3 cents to $16.96 in opening trading on the London
Stock Exchange, the shares jumped to $18.28 then settled back to
$18.19.
   Nestle has offered $3.9 billion for Rowntree.
</TEXT>
