<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Escape,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>East German Flees into West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An East German man today slipped
through his homeland's heavily fortified border and escaped to West
Germany, Bavarian authorities said.
   The man, identified only as a 27-year-old laborer, apparently
was not seen by armed communist guards who regularly patrol the
border separating the two German states. He was uninjured, state
police said.
   No other details were released on the flight, the fifth into
Bavaria state from East Germany this month.
   On Tuesday, West German officials said that two East Germans
recently died trying to escape to West Germany.
   The statement said one tried Monday to ram his car through a
steel gate at the Helmstedt checkpoint in East Germany. Authorities
last week found the body of another man who had apparently drowned
while trying to swim five miles across Luebeck Bay to West Germany,
the statement said.
