<HEAD>Flights Canceled in Maintenance Workers' Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British Airways canceled two flights to the
continent and combined others Wednesday because of a walkout by
3,500 maintenance workers at Heathrow Airport, company officials
said.
   The workers, who maintain and repair the firm's Heathrow-based
airplanes, walked off the job Monday to protest firing of a union
official.
   Flight disruptions were expected to worsen this weekend, a
three-day bank holiday.
   Both union and airline representatives said no talks were
planned in the walkout at the airport near London.
