<HEAD>Seniors Get Second Chance to Attend Prom</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At West Bloomfield High School's senior
prom, couples in tuxedos and evening gowns danced to jazz from the
1930s and '40s and thought of romance, nostalgia _ and bingo.
   The school's student leadership group organized Tuesday's prom
for people who missed their own prom or wanted to attend another.
   The age difference made things uneasy for at least one student.
   ``My date wants to know when bingo starts,'' one young lady said.
   Al Krusac missed taking his girlfriend, Clara, to their 1936
prom while stationed in Hawaii in the service. The Walled Lake
couple dressed in tuxedo and gown for Tuesday's dance.
   ``I had to wait 52 years to make it up to her,'' said Krusac,
72, of his wife of 50 years. ``I shout it to the world that I love
this woman.''
