<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Ford     05-25 0089</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Ford,0093</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ford Foundation Opens Office in Beijing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Ford Foundation has opened an office in
Beijing, its representative said Wednesday.
   The foundation expected to commit $4.5 million in China this
year, Ford's China representative Peter Geithner said at a
reception marking the opening.
   The Beijing office is the 14th overseas branch of the giant
foundation established in 1936 by American industrialist Henry Ford.
   The foundation gives grants to institutions and individuals for
projects on poverty, social justice, public policy, education,
culture and international affairs.
</TEXT>
