<HEAD>13 Dead in Indian Flooding</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Melting snow from the Himalayas
triggered flooding that inundated 52 villages, killed 13 people and
forced hundreds of families to flee to higher ground, it was
reported Wednesday.
   The flooding occurred along the Brahmaputra River and its
tributaries in the northeastern state of Assam, the United News of
India said.
   The river also flooded thousands of acres of farmland.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
