<1ST_LINE>r a AM-KidsSwindled     05-25 0259</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Kids Swindled,0265</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Kids' League Treasurer Sought With Missing Funds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GATLINBURG, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Little League Boosters Club is out
its $37,000 savings account and its treasurer, who's suspected of
taking the money.
   Club President Ernie Shultz said the apparent theft came to
light earlier this month when some of the club's checks bounced.
Treasurer Bobbi Sanor was asked to attend a meeting but didn't turn
up, he said.
   Police Chief Harry Montgomery said Ms. Sanor has not been seen
in town since the first week in May. An arrest warrant has been
issued charging Ms. Sanor with embezzlement.
   ``When we called the meeting and told her we wanted to see the
books, she said `no problem.' Then we met and she was gone, and
she'd taken her son out of school, too, '' Shultz said.
   Shultz said the club, which sponsors football, basketball and
cheerleading programs that last year involved about 200 youngsters,
is faced with $20,000 in unpaid bills.
   Shultz said Ms. Sanor was the club's treasurer in 1986 without
any problems. ``She worked real hard, I guess that's what stumped
everybody,'' he said. ``When you get somebody for volunteer work
who works that hard, you don't push them too much, you know. But
we'll be more careful in the future.''
   He said the club is going to become bonded and require two
signatures on all checks.
   He said the club will ``try to have fund-raisers and hope people
will give us money to pull through this. That's about all we can do
right now.''
</TEXT>
