<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ElvisShow     05-25 0245</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Elvis Show,0251</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Friend Says Vegas A Natural for Show on Presley's Life</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ROBERT MACY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The late Elivs Presley set attendance
records here that still stand, so it seems the most appropriate
city for a premiere of a show on the life of the king of rock 'n'
roll, a friend of his says.
   Jerry Schilling made the observation Tuesday night as the Las
Vegas Hilton unveiled plans for the stage show ``Elvis _ An
American Musical.''
   ``There's no more appropriate place to premiere a show on his
life,'' Schilling said. ``Elvis played here six weeks at a time,
twice a year. He loved this city.''
   Presley's attendance records at the Las Vegas Hilton remain
unbroken.
   The show's world premiere is scheduled July 1, with the
production running through Aug. 29. Producers plan to take the show
on the road to New Haven, Conn., Houston and Cleveland before the
premiere.
   The multimillion-dollar production will showcase 49 Presley
songs, using old film footage, laser lighting and a cast of 20,
including three people playing Presley at various stages in his
career.
   Schilling and Presley were neighbors in Memphis, Tenn., and
became friends. They worked together 11 years until Presley's death
Aug. 16, 1977.
   Today, Schilling has a talent management agency in Los Angeles.
He was a technical consultant on the television show ``Elvis and
Me'' and is working in a similar capacity on the stage show.
</TEXT>
