<HEAD>Two Killed, 11 Injured in Rebel Missile Attack, Tass Says</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Afghanistan, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebels fired missiles at two Afghan communities,
killing two people, wounding 11 and destroying a mosque, Tass said
Wednesday.
   The Soviet agency, quoting the Afghan news agency Bakhtar, said
the attacks were made on the city of Maymana in Fariab province and
Jaji-Maydan, a district in Paktia province. One missile made a
direct hit on a mosque in Jaji-Maydan, Tass said.
   Tass did not say when the attacks took place.
   Soviet soldiers began withdrawing from Afghanistan on May 15,
leaving forces of the pro-Soviet government of President Najib to
fight the rebels.
