<HEAD>WASHN: $15,001-$50,000.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   THOMAS CASS BALLENGER
   Income: $150,070-$168,070.
   Honoraria: $4,000.
   Gifts: None.
   Assets: $885,031-$1.675 million and up.
   Liabilities: $305,005-$725,000.
   Ballenger reported extensive stock, real estate and partnership
holdings. He reported capital losses and partnership losses of
$97,028 to $278,500, which more than offset capital gains during
the year and reduced his overall income. He is chairman of the
board of Plastic Packaging Inc. His holding in that company is
valued at more than $250,000.
   He was an active stock trader, reporting 91 transactions.
