   Roberts, a member of the House Agriculture Commitee, took a
fact-finding trip to Chicago that was paid for by the Chicago
Mercantile Exchange. In addition, the exchange and the Chicago
Board of Trade each provided $500 honorarium to Roberts.
</TEXT>
