<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Baptist television preachers disagreed
over whether scandal-toppled TV preachers Jimmy Swaggart and Jim
Bakker should be allowed to return to television preaching.
   The Rev. James Robison of Dallas, speaking on an ABC news
program, argued that through forgiveness the gospel offers ``whole
and total restoration on the platform and in the pulpit.''
   However, the Rev. Jerry Falwell of Lynchburg, Va., said clergy
have special responsibilities and ``we don't have the luxury of a
major, scandalous sin, and then going back into the pulpit.''
