<1ST_LINE>r f PM-Penney'sBuilding     05-25 0197</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Penney's Building,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Penney Sells New York Office Building for $350 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   J.C. Penney Co. Inc. officials say the company's
former headquarters office building in New York City was sold at a
$150 million profit.
   The retailing giant agreed to sell the 45-story building in
Manhattan to a partnership formed by Tishman Speyer Properties and
Trammel Crow Properties, Penney spokesman Duncan Muir said Tuesday.
   Penney is moving its headquarters to the Dallas suburb of Plano.
   William R. Howell, the chairman of Penney, said the building was
sold for $350 million, but the after-tax gain from the sale will
amount to about $150 million at the closing, which is scheduled for
early August.
   Real estate and financial experts had estimated in early 1987
that the building, which was assessed at $100 million for tax
purposes, was worth as much as $400 million.
   Penney moved into the building in 1964 as a major tenant and
purchased it in 1977 for about $40 million, Muir said.
   Penney officials announced in April 1987 that the company would
move its 2,200 management employees to the Dallas area to be closer
to the majority of Penney's 1,400 retail stores.
</TEXT>
