<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Unemployment,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Unemployment Rate Stays Stable At 10.4 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUXEMBOURG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The number of jobless in the 12 European
Economic Community nations totalled 16.3 million on March 30, down
340,000 from February, the EEC reported Wednesday.
   Despite this drop, Eurostat, the EEC's statistics agency, said
the March figure corresponded with a seasonally adjusted jobless
rate of 10.4 percent, a rate that has been unchanged since January.
   Eurostat said in seasonally unadjusted terms, unemployment fell
in all EEC nations in March, but the declines from February
differed greatly from country to country.
   It gave these seasonally unadjusted March unemployment figures
for the EEC member states, with the percentage drop from the
previous month in brackets:
   Belgium, 458,500 (3.7 percent); Denmark, 255,000 (2 percent);
France, 2.54 million (3.3 percent); Greece, 133,000 (7 percent);
Ireland, 247,100 (1.4 percent); Italy, 3.63 million (0.1 percent);
Luxembourg, 2,728 (8.8 percent); Netherlands, 686,900 (2 percent);
Portugal, 321,000 (1.6 percent); Spain, 2.99 million (1.5 percent);
Britain, 2.59 million (2.8 percent) and West Germany, 2.44 million
(3 percent).
</TEXT>
