<HEAD>Inspiration Resources To Sell Copper Subsidary For About $125
Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inspiration Resources Corp. said Wednesday it
had agreed to sell the assets of a copper-mining subsidiary to the
Cyprus Minerals Co. for about $125 million in cash.
   Inspiration said it expects to close the sale of its
Consolidated Copper Co. assets to the Englewood, Colo.-based Cyprus
by July 1, and that it intended to apply the net proceeds to retire
all of its current bank debt.
   That action will reduce the company's debt-to-capitalization
ratio ``from 42 percent at the year-end 1987 to less than 28
percent after the sale,'' said Reuben F. Richards, Inspiration's
chairman.
   The deal is subject to negotiation of a definitive agreement and
regulatory approvals, company officials said.
