<HEAD>Saatchi and Saatchi Profit Up 11 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Saatchi and Saatchi PLC said Wednesday its
earnings rose 10.9 percent in the first six months of its fiscal
year from a year earlier.
   The British advertising and consulting company said its earnings
totaled 34.6 million pounds, or $65 million, up from 31.2 million
pounds in the same period a year ago.
   Revenue rose 9.6 percent to 402.2 million pounds from 367
million pounds.
   The company said its results were hurt by the appreciation of
the pound, mostly against the U.S. dollar.
   Communication interests, which includes advertising, public
relations and marketing, contributed 45.3 million pounds to the
company's operating profit, up from 42.3 million pounds a year
earlier.
   Operating profit from consulting activities jumped to 8.8
million pounds from 6.3 million pounds.
   The company, which is not required to under British law, did not
break out quarterly profit.
