<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Closing,0137</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market closed mixed today in quiet
trading.
   Analysts said traders remained paralyzed, acknowledging that
recent corporate earnings have been stronger than expected, yet
fearful that interest rates could easily head higher.
   High interest rates hurt Wall Street by cutting into the
corporate profits that support stock prices, and by causing
investors to take money from stocks and put it into high-yielding
debt instruments.
   Traders' reluctance to act has meant that volume has been
particularly slow lately.
   Today's activity continued that trend, notable exceptions being
interest-sensitive issues, such as banks and insurance companies,
which showed healthy gains, and several other stocks related to
real or potential takeover moves or _ to a lesser extent _
dividend-recapture strategies.
