<FILEID>AP-NR-05-25-88 2225EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-Litton     05-25 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Litton,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Litton's Profit Up 22 Percent in Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Litton Industries Inc. reported
that its third-quarter profit rose 22 percent from a year earlier.
   The industrial giant said Wednesday that it earned $42 million,
or $1.60 a share, in its third quarter ended April 30, up from
$34.3 million, or $1.29 a share, a year earlier.
   Litton's businesses include defense systems, electronics and
industrial automation.
   Sales for the third quarter were $1.2 billion, up from $1.15
billion in the same period a year earlier.
   In the first nine months of its current fiscal year, Litton
earned $123.3 million, or $4.67 a share, up 20 percent from
earnings of $102.7 million, or $3.83 a share, a year earlier. Sales
for the first nine months were $3.55 billion, up from $3.19 billion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
